<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Genesis region hacking?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11926&amp;p=135174#p135174"><![CDATA[
Go to address $0001F0 in the ROM, then change the three bytes there to the ASCII string &quot;JUE&quot;. Yeah, that's pretty much all there's to it, most games with region lockout look at the ROM header instead of being hardcoded (that's what you get when everybody uses the off-the-shelf routine).<br /><br />A few games are hardcoded and that method won't work on those, in that case your only option is to hack the game itself =/ (and this procedure will be unique to each game).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4526">Sik</a> — Fri Oct 17, 2014 2:27 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
